      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STORMY DAY (8) trailed the lead and fought on well to be beaten 3.5 lengths into third (19.55) at Murray Bridge Straight in a Grade 5 over 350m. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Can find winning form. CABAO OPAL (5) made light work of the tricky draw with a fast early sectional but gathered in and had to settle for the minors, finishing third (23.26) at Gawler over 400m. Has never been out of the placings from four starts out of this box. Leading player again. RED EMPEROR (2) has shown good improvement at his last two starts, most recently finishing 3rd at this track over 530m. Bold showing expected. TENACIOUS DESIGN (7) hit the frame here last start so don't underestimate.",
